nt()`. Since `mint()` can accrue interest and mint at a higher exchange rate, internal `mintTokens` credit can exceed actual lTokens received.","impact":"Users can be credited with more internal investment than the protocol actually minted, enabling value extraction at others’ expense and potential insolvency.","paths":["supply -> read exchangeRateStored (stale) -> mint accrues interest/updates rate -> actual minted lTokens < internal mintTokens -> inflated totalInvestment"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Same-chain liquidation shortfall check re-applies index growth to already-accrued borrow value","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:238","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:347","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:350"],"claim":"`liquidateBorrow` passes `borrowed` from `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`, which already includes accrued borrow effects; `liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal` multiplies by `currentBorrowIndex / storedBorrowIndex` again, overstating debt in the shortfall test.","impact":"Accounts can be treated as undercollateralized earlier than intended, enabling premature/unfair liquidation.","paths":["liquidateBorrow -> getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral returns borrowed/collateral","liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal computes borrowedAmount = borrowed * currentIndex / borrowBalance.borrowIndex","borrowedAmount becomes inflated -> `borrowedAmount > collateral` may pass for positions that should not be liquidatable"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain borrow aggregation can hard-revert when both direction records coexist","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:83","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:84","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:485","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:641","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:718"],"claim":"`borrowWithInterest` reverts if both `crossChainBorrows` and `crossChainCollaterals` are non-empty for a user/token. Opposite-direction cross-chain borrowing for the same underlying can populate both arrays on one chain, violating this assumption.","impact":"Borrow/liquidity/liquidation/repay flows that depend on borrow aggregation can revert, creating permissionless DoS and potentially locking user positions.","paths":["Direction A->B borrow creates `crossChainBorrows` on chain A for token X","Direction B->A borrow creates `crossChainCollaterals` on chain A for token X","Any call path invoking borrowWithInterest for that user/token reverts with invariant violation"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Unchecked ERC20 `transfer` can update protocol state without actual token payout","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:170","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:204"],"claim":"Payout paths use raw `IERC20.transfer` and ignore its boolean return value. For non-standard ERC20s that return `false` instead of reverting, execution continues and state changes persist despite failed transfer.","impact":"Users can be debited/indebted without receiving tokens, and protocol accounting can diverge from real token balances.","paths":["redeem/borrow/borrowForCrossChain performs stateful actions and calls raw transfer","token returns false (no revert)","function continues, leaving accounting changed but payout not delivered"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-012","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain repay lookup is ambiguous and keyed only by srcEid","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:397","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:406","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:539"],"claim":"`_getBorrowDetails` selects a collateral position using only `srcEid` within `crossChainCollaterals[borrower][underlying]`. If multiple positions share the same source chain but differ by other identifiers (e.g., source token), repayment can update the wrong position.","impact":"Repayments can be misattributed, corrupting debt records and impairing liquidation/accounting correctness.","paths":["Borrower has multiple cross-chain collateral records for same borrowed underlying with identical srcEid","repayCrossChainBorrow -> _getBorrowDetails picks first srcEid match","_updateRepaymentState and DestRepay message mutate/propagate wrong position data"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-013","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain liquidation health check uses seize amount as synthetic new borrow","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:273","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:276","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:431","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:433"],"claim":"When validating liquidation on the collateral chain, `_checkLiquidationValid` calls `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` with `borrowAmount = payload.amount`, but `payload.amount` is seizeTokens (collateral quantity), not pending debt. This distorts shortfall evaluation.","impact":"Liquidation eligibility can be misclassified, enabling liquidation of positions that are not actually underwater or causing inconsistent liquidation behavior.","paths":["Chain B computes seizeTokens and sends CrossChainLiquidationExecute with payload.amount = seizeTokens","Chain A _checkLiquidationValid treats payload.amount as hypothetical additional borrow","Borrowed-vs-collateral comparison is based on a wrong variable and can return true for otherwise healthy accounts"],"round":2,"source_agents":["merge_layer","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-014","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"LEND rewards can be claimed repeatedly because accrued balances are never decremented","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:399","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:402","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:416","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:76"],"claim":"`claimLend` reads `lendStorage.lendAccrued(holder)` and transfers that amount via `grantLendInternal`, but never writes back a reduced accrued value. The same accrued balance remains claimable on repeated calls.","impact":"Any account with non-zero accrued rewards can repeatedly claim and drain LEND held by the router, including rewards attributable to other users.","paths":["User accrues positive `lendAccrued` once","User calls `claimLend` and receives full accrued amount","`lendAccrued[user]` is unchanged","User repeats claims until router LEND balance is exhausted"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Liquidity checks accept zero oracle prices, creating fail-open borrow authorization","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:431","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:445","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:460","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:152","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617"],"claim":"`getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` uses oracle prices without validating `price > 0`. If a market price returns `0`, borrow-side effects for that asset become `0`, and collateral checks can pass despite real economic risk.","impact":"During oracle outages/misconfiguration returning zero, users can borrow assets with effectively no borrow value added in checks, potentially extracting pool liquidity and creating bad debt.","paths":["Oracle returns 0 price for borrow market","User calls same-chain or cross-chain borrow","Borrow value contribution is computed as zero in liquidity check","Borrow proceeds while true collateralization is insufficient"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Borrow/redeem update accounting after external calls, leaving reentrancy window for callback-capable tokens","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:121","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:127","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:167","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:170","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:179"],"claim":"`redeem` and `borrow` perform external protocol/token calls before updating internal accounting (`totalInvestment`, `borrowBalance`), and no reentrancy guard exists. Callback-capable listed tokens can reenter while state is stale.","impact":"If a callback-capable market token is listed, an attacker contract may chain nested operations against stale balances to over-redeem/over-borrow relative to intended single-call limits.","paths":["Attacker triggers `borrow` or `redeem` via contract","External token/protocol call executes before accounting update","Callback reenters router and passes checks using stale state","Nested operations extract excess value"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain repay path incorrectly mutates same-chain borrow storage","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:472","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:475","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:492","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:497","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:425"],"claim":"Cross-chain repay flows call `CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal(..., _isSameChain=false)`, but the function always writes to same-chain `borrowBalance` (`removeBorrowBalance`/`updateBorrowBalance`) after repayment. This mixes cross-chain repayment results into same-chain debt storage.","impact":"Debt accounting becomes inconsistent: liabilities can be double-counted (same-chain + cross-chain) causing false shortfall/DoS/unfair liquidation, and full cross-chain repay can erase same-chain borrow records for the same market if present.","paths":["repayCrossChainBorrowInternal -> _handleRepayment -> CoreRouter.repayCrossChainLiquidation","CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal computes borrowedAmount from cross-chain path (`borrowWithInterest`)","function still updates/removes `borrowBalance[borrower][_lToken]` (same-chain slot)","Cross-chain state is also updated in `_updateRepaymentState`, creating divergent or duplicated debt state"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-018","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation uses seized-collateral quantity