fer from liquidator)","Cross-chain execution reaches failure branch and sends `LiquidationFailure`","Destination `_handleLiquidationFailure` transfers `payload.amount` to liquidator from router balance"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation health check uses stale seize amount as synthetic borrow","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-013 (same root cause and affected logic)."},{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation execute lacks borrower debt validation before seize","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not independently reportable: liquidation initiation on the debt chain already requires an existing cross-chain borrow record and bounded repay amount before sending execute message."},{"title":"Unchecked array bounds in claimLend can cause out-of-gas DOS","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Permissionless caller choosing huge arrays mainly self-DoSes their own transaction; no durable protocol-wide DoS state change is created."},{"title":"setCrossChainRouter allows immediate router swap without timelock","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Governance/trust-model concern (owner power), not a code-level vulnerability under assumed privileged-owner model."},{"title":"Cross-chain repay allows partial repay of already-removed collateral","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Insufficient evidence of a concrete exploit path from current code; described inconsistency is speculative without a demonstrated reachable state transition."}]}
